h3. Issue Summary

When we set up a header text within a table and click over a link to this header, if the table header has multiple lines of text, it will occlude the table row.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a page;
 # Insert the [Table of Contents|https://support.atlassian.com/confluence-cloud/docs/insert-the-table-of-contents-macro/] macro;
 # Generate 5 paragraphs of some [lorem ipsum|https://www.lipsum.com/feed/html] text, so we have a scrollable page;
 # Insert a table;
 # In the table header, insert some text that makes it have ~3 lines;
 # In the next table row, insert a single word and set it up to be a header 2, for example;
 # Publish the page;
 # Set your browser window to do not be full-screened, and make it to be a bit cropped;
 # In the ToC macro, click on the header link.

h3. Expected Results

You got to the header text you set within the table.
h3. Actual Results

You do get where the header text is, but the table header is occluding it:

!CONFCLOUD-72904.gif|width=939,height=488!

*Notes*
* It might be reproducible in full screen if the monitor is a bit small (like 13", for example);
* If the table has more rows than what can be fit in the browser view (even if it is in full-screen), this bug also occurs.

h3. Workaround

You can go full-screen on your browser to avoid this behavior.

h3. Issue Summary

On adding the @top-right custom header rule as a part of PDF Stylesheet under the Space and then exporting the space does not work correctly. The border around it confirms that it is aligned well within the boundaries of the page which is incorrect.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 * As a part of PDF Stylesheet option under Space Tools -> Look and Feel -> PDF StyleSheet, add below stylesheet

{code:java}
 @page
 {

border:2px solid yellow;

@top-right
{ border:2px solid black; }

@top-center
{ border:2px solid green; }

@top-left
{ border:2px solid red; }

}
{code}
 * Export space as PDF.

h3. Expected Results

@top-right custom header border should be aligned to the extreme right of the page.
h3. Actual Results

@top-right custom header border is not aligned to the extreme right of the page.
h3. Workaround

Add following into the page tag:
{code:java}
@page
{
padding-right: 0px;
padding-left: 0px;
} 
{code}

h3. Issue Summary

Currently when a page is shared the notification title is as below:
{code:java}
<persons name> shared a page with you{code}
Previously the share page notifications would include the name of the group the page with shared with similar to below:
{code:java}
<Persons name> shared a page with <group>{code}
Many teams would benefit if the notification title would include a list of users/groups that the page was shared with.
h3. Workaround

Include the users/groups in the custom text box that appears when sharing a page.

h3. Issue Summary
When we set up a custom field to be called "_Version_" on JIRA, this field won't be shown in a JIRA macro - not as it is named, at least.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Go to *JIRA > Settings > Issues > Custom Fields*;
# Create a custom field (single line or number, for example) and call it "_Version_";
# Add this custom field to the project you wish;
# Create a JIRA issue in this project;
# Go to Confluence and create a page;
# Insert the JIRA macro with the following JQL: {{project = <PKEY>}};
# In the *Display Options*, add the custom field you just created to be shown;
# Click over the *Insert* button.

h3. Expected Results
The selected fields will be displayed.

h3. Actual Results
Instead of showing the _Version_ one, it shows a column called "_Affected Version/S_", with empty information.

*Notes*
* If there is information in the _Version_ field of your JIRA issues, it won't be displayed anyway.

h3. Workaround
Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available, so avoid naming your custom fields as "_Version_".

h3. Issue Summary
 - User created a Page, but is no longer a watcher but is still receiving notification about it under Bell icon

h3. Steps to Reproduce

 - _User A_ needs to create a page in a Confluence Space;
 - _User B_ needs to add some comments, mentions, Likes so _User A_ can receive notifications about it;
 - _User A_ is no longer a watcher and is supposed to stop receiving notifications;
 - Any other actions that generates a Notification is still being showed up under Bell icon;

h3. Expected Results
 - Notifications shouldn’t be delivered to pages you’re not a watcher of

h3. Actual Results
- User is still receiving notifications about pages they’ve created

h3. Workaround
Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Issue Summary
After a recent correction we have applied, where when we added files to a table within a third-party macro it would keep bouncing the page, now the file preview thumbnail gets greyed.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Make sure you have a third-party app installed that provides a bodied macro, like [TableFilters|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/apps/27447/table-filter-and-charts-for-confluence?hosting=cloud&tab=overview], for example;
# Create a page;
# Add the TableFilter macro;
# Within this macro, add a table;
# Within this table, add a PDF file;
# Publish the page.

h3. Expected Results
The file is previewed with a clear thumbnail.

h3. Actual Results
It turns into a grey box with the file name.

h3. Workaround
Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

Currently, calling the [Get user|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/confluence/rest/api-group-users/#api-wiki-rest-api-user-get] endpoint in Confluence Cloud returns the following:
{code:java}
"profilePicture":{
    "path":"/wiki/aa-avatar/557058:6b9c9931-4693-49c1-8b3a-931f1af98134",
    "width":48,
    "height":48,
    "isDefault":false
}{code}
This path is relative to the current confluence tenant, and resolves to this full URL via a 302 redirect:

[https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6b9c9931-4693-49c1-8b3a-931f1af98134/7f0c6294-4750-4ff7-a6cb-be6b43744fc5/128]

Wheras calling the [Get user|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/api-group-users/#api-rest-api-3-user-get] endpoint in Jira cloud returns the following, with existing full URLs at different sizes:
{code:java}
"avatarUrls":{
    "48x48":"https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6b9c9931-4693-49c1-8b3a-931f1af98134/7f0c6294-4750-4ff7-a6cb-be6b43744fc5/48",
    "24x24":"https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6b9c9931-4693-49c1-8b3a-931f1af98134/7f0c6294-4750-4ff7-a6cb-be6b43744fc5/24",
    "16x16":"https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6b9c9931-4693-49c1-8b3a-931f1af98134/7f0c6294-4750-4ff7-a6cb-be6b43744fc5/16",
     "32x32":"https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6b9c9931-4693-49c1-8b3a-931f1af98134/7f0c6294-4750-4ff7-a6cb-be6b43744fc5/32"
} {code}
It would be great if Confluence cloud could add this avatarUrls property to the the user response models, both to enhance consistency between Atlassian products, and also to make it easier to display Confluence avatars in Forge applications (which currently include a CSP for [avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net|https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/] but not for the current Confluence tenant - thus requiring developers to add *.atlassian.net to their [external domains egress|https://developer.atlassian.com/platform/forge/add-content-security-and-egress-controls])
